[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

Data by country, area, or territory for 30 Sep 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesSept30_1601553676.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 33.3% of daily case numbers and 36.1% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, maintaining its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 16.5 million cases. The USA and Brazil remain dominant, followed by Argentina, Colombia, Peru, and Mexico. Other countries reporting more than 1000 new cases in the past 24 hours include Chile and Canada.

- The European region reported 20.0% of daily case numbers and 16.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 5.8 million. Countries not reporting cases today (30 Sep 2020) include Spain, Israel, and Kazakhstan. The dominant country is Russia followed by the France, UK, Ukraine, Netherlands, and Czech Republic. Other countries reporting more than 1000 new cases in the past 24 hours include Germany, Italy, Romania, Turkey, Poland, and Germany.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 7.4% of daily case numbers and 9.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of greater than 2.3 million cases. Iraq remains the dominant country, followed by Iran, Morocco, Lebanon, Libya, Jordan, Pakistan, UAE, Oman, and Palestinian Authority.

- The African region reported 1.6% of daily case numbers and 2.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.1 million cases. South Africa is again the dominant country, followed by Ethiopia, Mozambique, Ghana, Uganda, Kenya, Nigeria, and Algeria. However, all reporting countries reported less than 1000 cases.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 2.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.61 million cases. The Philippines continues to dominate, followed by Japan, South Korea, and Malaysia.

- The South East Asia region reported 36.5% of the daily newly reported cases and 32.3% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.9 million cases. India continues to dominate followed by Indonesia, Nepal, Bangladesh, and Myanmar.

Today's report from Europe has weekend reporting artifact with key countries not reporting new cases in the past 24 hours. That being said, Europe is experiencing resurgences in many countries related to loosening restrictions and the summer vacation period. The Americas continue to have more countries reporting cases although there is a muting consisting with weekend artifact. Major transmission is also ongoing in South East Asia, specifically India, but other countries are following suit. - Cases are increasing in Nepal and Myanmar.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 30 Sep 2020 is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

